caption: Nice little Cafe. Thought it was completely different from when we searched in Maps than when we arrived but overall very happy with visit while in town. Very friendly staff. The food was delicious.
Not only is the food delicious, the staff so nice, they are involved in providing food for people in need. Just an Awesome company.
Great espresso and sandwiches

Meh. Found their pot pie they brag about being just a clump of dough, chicken, a carrot or two, and a few peas. The crust was soggy and the flavor was bland. Took 3 bites and gave up. Felt like I was eating Stage 3 baby food.

Ordered take out breakfast. I had biscuits and gravy, sausage patties and bacon. The bacon was perfect and exactly crispy enough but not too much. The biscuits and gravy are among the best I have ever consumed.  The biscuits were cooked perfectly and had just a hint of sweetness. Everything is very nice

Cafe Moxo offers fresh, original food that never disappoints. We especially enjoy their specials and often mix that up with tried and true selections.  Above and beyond their outstanding food, they give generously to the community. In the worst of times, Moxo helped others and worked to maintain staff.
Interesting sandwiches on excellent breads!
I have tried something new every time I go here and have not found anything bad. I really like this place.
Great Food, Good Prices, and Just an Excellent Company All Together.
Fantastic comfort food with amazing service, a can’t skip place for lunch!!
One of, if not the best Cafe's in Springfield! Great food, cute building, and most importantly, caring owners and staff. Highly recommend!

We ordered the avocado toast and giddy up breakfast sandwich with coffee and cookies. Both the toast and sandwich were very tasty with standout sauces/fillings, although the bread and bagel themselves were a little lackluster. The cookies are definitely not to be missed! We got the brean and double chocolate.

Ordered take out breakfast. I had biscuits and gravy, sausage patties and bacon. The bacon was perfect and exactly crispy enough but not too much. The biscuits and gravy are among the best I have ever consumed.  The biscuits were cooked perfectly and had just a hint of sweetness.  The gravy was white gravy "Okie style."  Cooked perfectly!
Great service and food.
Went yesterday and had a mocha and chocolate chip cookie, both were excellent! As well as the service, very prompt and friendly. Will definitely be back.
Moxo is always fantastic. Great food, great service. One of my Top 3 restaurants in Springfield!
First time. Great experience!
Chic little spot with great food

We ate here twice when we visited Springfield to see some of the Lincoln sites. There are not many places open downtown now with the covid virus going on. This place has a nice lunch menu and breakfast menu. You order at the counter and they will bring to your table. It appears that they also have a brisk takeout business.
These folks go above and beyond and do so much for the community
Excellent food, and service.

I had the Giddy Up breakfast sandwich and it was fantastic. The cranberry biscuit (scone?) was flaky and not too sweet, a nice contrast to my coffee. Staff were nice and social distancing was observed. Wonderful place. Great service and nice people. Highly recommend!! You will be amazed at how good it is!

Easily one of the best breakfasts I've ever had in Springfield. This place is a rare, slightly hidden, little favorite of mine. Never been disappointed & they give back to our community regularly. Support local ❤

Cafe Moxo has been a mainstay of downtown Springfield for years now. It's a great spot for a quick breakfast or lunch, or even just a coffee in between. The menu is a mix of cafe standards and novel items. The pot pie is a local favorite. Though prices have increased in recent years, I find the quality to be worth what I pay.
Good different menu items.
This is walking distance from my work.  Will be a weekly lunch spot for me.
Awesome service, piping hot coffee, and delicious sandwiches! Highly recommend the Cuban, it was incredible!
Best homemade chicken noodle soup ever!!!! The cookies and the people who work their are amazing too!
My wife and I have eaten here a couple of times. The food is delicious but pricey.
One my favorite 💛 Breakfast and lunch spots! Always good service, they even brung me some gravy, when I didn't have none for my biscuits. Glad you're still OPEN please patronize this local business.
Food is good, staff are very accommodating but they need more spacious place.
Best Cafe in Springfield.

I absolutely love this cafe! Great customer service, clean, friendly environment, and no long wait! Not many vegan options unfortunately but they do offer vegetarian options. I grabbed an iced turtle 🐢 mocha and a fresh fruit cup! 😋
Friendly. The food is good.

All of the yum!  There truly is nothing to NOT love about this place except maybe they aren't open in the evenings so I can eat there and drink at Buzzbomb across the street!  (And I think they were gonna try pre-covid? They do combine for brunch...)  Food is VERY good.  My family reports the best chicken and beef pot pies in the city.  AND they pay their employees decent wages, so they get me as a lifelong customer because of their employment practices.
Very nice restaurant
So amazing! Such culture! So yummy

We especially like the care that Cafe Moxo is taking these days.  The kitchen and wait staff wear masks.  A sign prominently on the front door asks patrons to wear masks too.  We didn't see anyone coming or going without a mask.  Hand sanitizer is conveniently available too. great
They where playing house music and the food was awesome.. Really good time

Very good food. A different way to order— there are boards that are kind of hard to read. (Maybe get some low tech menu boards on the wall that people in line can read?) Anyway, the food was great, not cheap but worth it. Recommend!

The portabella mushroom sandwich and the tomato soup were very delicious. However, the chicken pot pie was so bad that our dog wouldn't even eat it. It was gummy, no chicken, tasted like mushy goo and the crust is best left undescribed. The cookies were good, but I have had far better and the chicken salad sandwich was at best mediocre. Then being charged $1.25 for a cup of water was over the top. If they are going for vegetarian...then do it and leave the other food groups alone.  Those two items (tomato soup and portabella sandwich) were at least good.
Great spot to grab breakfast in downtown Springfield.

Overrated food(not bad though), great staff seriously.

The best breakfast we ever had! Truthfully....the Breakfast Burrito was amazing, never had a Burrito  this great at any place; also had the egg and sausage on ciabatta it was above & beyond the very best.  We're from New York formerly and  now live in California and this is truly  a five star plus breakfast place. Don't miss out on dining here.  Outstanding!!
Good stuff
Excellent food. Great service & very conscious of cleaning due to COVID-19.  They work really hard.  Keep it up! Thanks.

Cafe Moxo has very involved leadership. They step up to the plate to ensure their customers are safe. This locations is usually busy but the staff are very attentive. Breakfast burrito is some of the best in the business. Cookies, coffee and tea lock this place in the memory Bank.

Food was fine, but customers on either side of me while ordering did not wear masks. They were not asked to wear masks by staff person. I'd like to continue patronizing this restaurant. PLEASE FOLLOW CITY ORDINANCES. PLEASE DO NOT ADMIT OR SERVE PEOPLE WHO ARE NOT KEEPING OTHERS SAFE.
everyone work masks! it was super clean and they even wiped down my card before handing it back to me!

Too delicious not to sample prior to taking a photo! Fast, fresh and friendly! Very nice decor and vibe too. We had the avocado toast and baked egg with bacon. Cookie and coffee were great too! Definitely would be back if I lived near here.

I am glad that the restaurant is there and open given all that has happened. But I did not enjoy my meal at all I can't imagine what they did to make it so not tasty. I will go back for the coffee. It might just be me many people really really enjoy their offerings.
This is a GENUINE 5-Star review. Staff is very nice/friendly, the cold brew is great, and the sandwiches slap so hard! The meat at moxo was recommended to me and I'm so glad I ordered it!

Fantastic local Cafe. If you've never tried it, make sure you do when you come downtown.

Quick service, good food & the service is even better. The manager, Brandon, was super friendly & makes sure you had a quality experience, whether you’re a regular or traveling through town, like me. His associates Courtney and Patrick were also phenomenal. I highly recommend this establishment, will stop by if I find myself in Springfield again.

This is a small business to be sure and support during the Stay-at-Home order. Our favorite thing to order is a late breakfast; the sandwiches are always hot, fruit cups and bakery items are fresh. Everything carries nicely from the restaurant to our house.

Very good lunch today at Cafe Moxo.  I had soup and half a sandwich.  The interior decorations were nice and the staff very friendly.   There was a wide selection on the menu of unique items.  I would definitely go there again.  The restaurant is very convenient to downtown Springfield and easy to get to.

Edit: For full disclosure purposes, I'm keeping the original up. I did not take their offer to make things right. Last time I ordered barbecue, but got buffalo. I may not have said it clearly at the time.  This time I did an online order. Not only was my order correct this time, my food was ready way before the "order ready by" time. Ordering and pickup was simple. The staff were very friendly. I highly recommend Cafe Moxo  Original Review: Great place with fair prices. They lost one star for messing up my order, but even though I normally dislike what they gave me, I still enjoyed it. I'll definitely be going back soon.

I went here 2 days in a row while visiting Springfield and it was a great choice. My first day I ordered a breakfast sandwich and a latte, which were very tasty. I sat and relaxed in the cafe for a while and watched the farmers market outside. The second day I was in more of a rush and just wanted my drink; I went in to find it bustling and everyone very busy. Despite this, the person I assume to be the manager, as well as two others employees recognized me immediately and remembered my drink order without even asking. They made it as soon as they could so that I didn’t have to wind through the food line. I was really impressed. Good stuff, guys. Keep it going.
